post: {'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The legalization of drugs deprives criminals of a substantial source of their income. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Various currently illegal drugs have valuable medical properties; these substances may have the potential to solve problems in our society such as mental health issues. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Giving a legal framework to the use of certain drugs may help to prevent the development of infectious diseases.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Evidence suggests that [addiction is not caused by drugs](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ao8L-0nSYzg) but by social problems.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "Legalisation of cigarettes [did not stop](https://thedebrief.co.uk/news/real-life/1-every-7-british-cigarettes-contraband-counterfeit/) illicit and poor quality cheaper versions. That's why legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Since everything is legal, users can instead choose the drugs with the most benefits and the least harms.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Legalising drug use would not significantly increase the consumption of drugs. That's why all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The human body is very complex; a given drug can have quite subtle aspects. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Young people could use fake IDs to buy drugs, the same way they currently do with alcohol and cigarettes.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Under the influence of drugs, users are more likely to commit immoral acts.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'There will be less smuggling and less drug-caused conflict. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Nearly all negative effects of addicts on their families are not fueled by the addiction itself, but the fact that the drug they are addicted to is made illegal by the ban on drugs. I think all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalizing all drugs will be seen as a sign of the government/authority giving up on protecting people from the harm they could do, to themselves and others, through poorly selected drug use.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'This does not take into account plants that do not grow well everywhere. For these cases, there is still a reliance on other communities that fall under different legislation to cultivate the plants. This keeps a connection with the international criminal drug trade.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Lack of regulation](https://www.drugabuse.gov/drugs-abuse/opioids/opioid-overdose-crisis#three) has been a significant cause of the opioid crisis.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Governments would be able to check what cutting agents are used within the drugs, meaning they will be safer as potentially harmful cutting agents would be banned. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': '[In German law](http://www.emcdda.europa.eu/countries/drug-reports/2018/germany/drug-laws-and-drug-law-offences_en), the use of drugs is not mentioned as a legal offense.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drug prohibition might be inspired by some kind of racism but abandoning it would not necessarily mean an improvement of the situation for those incarcerated or addicted to drugs. There are still many other systematic racial issues unrelated to drug prohibition.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The patient and/or friends won't, to avoid prosecution, say what the drugs were. That's why all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The logic of this argument would necessitate prohibition of alcohol, along with cigarettes, prescription painkillers, household cleaning products, motor vehicles, power tools; and anything a person may use to end their life consciously or accidentally. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'US states that have legalised marijuana have seen a lot of benefits.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Through legalising drugs within a finite border, the criminal economic chain could be controlled inside that border only.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Mexico](https://www.globalresearch.ca/destabilizing-mexico/12707) has been destabilized by drug cartel activities such as lawlessness, kidnappings, increasing corruption and frequent assassinations.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'There are legal substances which have a much higher toxicity and legal substances which can be developed to be highly toxic. The possible use of drugs as weapons is irrelevant as there are much more dangerous substances freely available.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Based on countries that have decriminalized drugs like [Portugal](https://borgenproject.org/decriminalization-of-drugs-in-portugal/), drug use has not significantly increased among the poor population, or at all.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "The reason for black market chemicals to be cheaper, is that the black market doesn't care about cost incurring legal restrictions and taxes. I think drugs should remain illegal."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The cigarette industry suppressed research that demonstrated the carcinogenicity of cigarettes \\([pg. 2](https://www.who.int/tobacco/media/en/TobaccoExplained.pdf)\\).'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'When obtaining drugs legally people can be sure that the drugs are pure and accurately measured. With the illegal drug market drugs are often mis-sold, inaccurately measured or cut with other substances.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Regulations that prohibit working under the influence of alcohol can trivially be expanded to include all drugs. That's why all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drugs may be adulterated despite legalisation, like [alcoholic beverages.](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/20959682) I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Criminals will face competition from legal growers with lower shipping costs, which will drive prices down.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'People in poor health or overdosing on drugs are often not taken to receive medical attention for fear of criminal prosecution.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legal cultivation/production of psychoactive compounds on the personal or even community scale could eliminate the international black market for them, making society safer for communities.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'True freedom of choice means that individuals must face the consequences of their actions, whether they are good or bad. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Making things safer is always preferable.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Established companies selling drugs could be just as dangerous \\(to society\\) as criminals.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In 2014, [8.7%](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-healthcare-costs-smoking-idUSKBN0JX2BE20141219) of all healthcare spending in the US was spent on tobacco-related illnesses.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'There have been [no positive consequences](http://fileserver.idpc.net/library/Shadow%20Report_FINAL_ENGLISH.pdf) as a result of the war on drugs. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Many currently illegal drugs make substantial positive contributions to human culture. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Several 'great' artists have died from an overdose on drugs and thus actually causing negative contributions to human culture as the world is deprived of their 'artwork'."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'There is [no/little research](https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/309735.php) regarding the long-term effects of salvia.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In the Andes, [coca](https://nacla.org/article/beat-goes-us-war-coca), a sacred plant harmful when mass produced as a cash crop, has replaced the production of fruits and vegetables.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'A victim of such an act would not fear prosecution for consumption if drugs were legal, and therefore would more easily seek and obtain help and/or retribution.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Dangerous substitute drugs will be contained. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'This limits what we know about these compounds as well as to what length we are able to develop treatments for those struggling with addiction \\(physical and mental\\) as well as treatment for acute toxicity.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "In a truly free society self regulation should be our privilege. You are free to not use drugs, and you should be just as free to use them. That's why all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If legalised, drug users could be less likely to leave dangerous paraphernalia \\(broken pipes, syringes, etc.\\) behind in public places as the fear of criminal penalties for the possession of drug paraphernalia would no longer be an issue. This would lessen risk of disease and injury. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Children of addicts may be raised in an environment which makes it [likelier for them](https://www.samhsa.gov/data/sites/default/files/report_3223/ShortReport-3223.html) to consume and become addicts in the future.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalization will facilitate access to drugs.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug legalisation would mean governments get to suggest a recommended dose, preventing the incidence of death by overdose. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'A part of the "forbidden fruit" effect is that drugs provide short-term benefit \\(the "high"\\) in exchange for long-term cost \\(negative health impacts\\).'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'If a government wanted to put money into harm reduction, it could do so without legalising drugs in order to avoid the costs of enforcing a drug prohibition. It could instead cut other government programs.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'While neither seems acceptable, most would rather face prejudice than prison. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will remove the taboo that drug addiction currently carries with it. As a result, addicts will no longer be a target of prejudice. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Nearly all negative effects of addicts on their families are not fueled by the addiction itself, but the fact that the drug they are addicted to is made illegal by the ban on drugs. I think all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "In a truly free society self regulation should be our privilege. You are free to not use drugs, and you should be just as free to use them. That's why all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drug use negatively affects job performance.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will help contain the dangerous drug cartels. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Having drugs be both illegal and valuable has funded extensive infrastructure for smuggling things across the US border.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalizing drugs will help treat addicts. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Many drugs have a long history of responsible use within their historical context.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Inappropriate recreational drug use has negative health consequences. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'This is because the US prison system is [privately owned.](https://smartasset.com/mortgage/the-economics-of-the-american-prison-system) Incentive structures mean that running prisons can only be profitable with high rates of incarceration.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'A large portion of the public is irresponsible. Giving everyone the opportunity to use \\(or abuse\\) drugs would have negative consequences on these individuals.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalizing something means including it the current system of business oversight and regulation as other legal activities. This means documenting purchases and monetary transactions, as well as filing and paying taxes. This means more control over where drugs come from and money goes, rather than would be the case under prohibition or decriminalization.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Some drugs are toxic at very low doses. These drugs can rightfully be considered weapons as well as intoxicants.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Assuming that drugs will still be legally forbidden for people under a certain age, the distribution points will not be allowed to sell it to children.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Affordable drugs will more likely lessen the negative impacts of drug use, as overall users would be less likely to abuse substances due to psychological distress caused by financial instability.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drugs are insanely profitable at a relatively low level of effort, as opposed to other crimes.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Without proper education, people who are more prone to drug addiction may be more likely to get addicted to a drug.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The ban on drugs hinders scientific and, in particular, medical progress.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Benzodiazepines are [readily available](http://w-bad.org/statistics/) in most countries for common complaints like insomnia, jet lag and performance anxiety, and are actually more effective at increasing the effects of alcohol than barbiturates.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The violence associated with alcohol was far greater during the prohibition when it was banned. The National Bureau of Economic Research says: "[increases in enforcement of drug and alcohol prohibition have been associated with increases in the homicide rate](https://www.nber.org/papers/w6950)".'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'When obtaining drugs legally people can be sure that the drugs are pure and accurately measured. With the illegal drug market drugs are often mis-sold, inaccurately measured or cut with other substances.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The legalization of drugs will create jobs \\(i.e. people selling in certified shops, people in labs etc.\\).'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Governments invested a lot of money trying to cease drug use by everyone. It failed miserably. Not only it is not the most efficient way, but it is not even achievable.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "In a truly free society self regulation should be our privilege. You are free to not use drugs, and you should be just as free to use them. That's why all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If only leaving syringes was punishable, and not use or possession of drugs, they would put in the extra effort to _not_ break the law at all. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug legalisation may reduce the price of drugs. This would have positive effects. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalizing all drugs will lead to much larger societal rifts: Drug usage is higher among the poor and socially marginalized, which in turn makes their condition worse.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The correlation between drug use and crime is fuelled at least partly by prohibition.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'It is possible that decriminalization dissuades those who specifically start using drugs as a way of breaking the law, such as [early data from Portugal](https://www.leafly.com/news/politics/portugal-drug-decriminalization-statistics) suggests. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The additional tax revenue from drug commerce can be used to fund therapies and treatments. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The legalization of all drugs gives the possibility to control the age group of people participating in the drugs. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "A society where everyone consumes moderate amounts of drugs wouldn't be much different than the societies of today. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The ban on drugs has led to medical discrimination.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'There are more effective policies than legalizing drug use to challenge drug abuse.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'This is an argument against incarceration for drug related crimes, not for the outright legalisation of drugs. I believe legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'People may drive under the influence of drugs or make other decisions with public consequences.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drugs could be legalised in government shops in which they could be administered through government pharmacists. This would allow governments to control access, much like the [Swedish alcohol trade](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Systembolaget).'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The ban on drugs inflates its price, which, in turn, promotes distributors to mix it with sometimes dangerous chemical substances to augment its volume.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If drugs being illegal prevented addiction, there would be no drug addicted person. Thus, there is no prevention by just keeping drugs illegal. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': '"Profit for companies" is better than "profit for criminal cartels", if those are the two choices.'}
